A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 4 of Article 6 of Chapter 3 of Title 12 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to the Stone Mountain Memorial Association, so as to revise the purpose
3 of the association; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
4 purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Part 4 of Article 6 of Chapter 3 of Title 12 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
8 relating to the Stone Mountain Memorial Association, is amended by revising Code Section
9 12-3-192.1, relating to the purpose of the association, as follows:
10 "12-3-192.1.
11 The purposes of the Stone Mountain Memorial Association shall include:
12 (1) To preserve the natural areas situated within the Stone Mountain Park area;
13 (2) To provide access to Stone Mountain for Georgia's citizens; and
14 (3) To maintain an appropriate and suitable memorial for the Confederacy To educate
15 the public about the natural history of the mountain and its environment, and the history
16 of human interaction with the mountain and its surroundings."
